<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Classic Shell right click not working Windows 10]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6802&amp;p=29242#p29242"><![CDATA[
It can be due to a shell extension DLL that is installed. You could temporarily uninstall Classic Shell and see if the problem goes away. Classic Shell preserves its settings in the Registry even if it is uninstalled. If not, then your issue isn't related to Classic Shell. You could try doing a System Restore to an older date when your system was working OK.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Wed Sep 07, 2016 11:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
